DOM Manipulation:-
  It refers to the process of, dynamically modifying the Document Object Model (DOM),
  DOM is a web page using programming languages like JavaScript. 
  The DOM represents the structure of a web page as a tree of objects,
  where each node corresponds to a part of the page, such as elements, attributes, or text.

DOM manipulation allows developers to:
  > Change content, styles, or attributes of elements.
  > Add, remove, or rearrange elements.
  > Respond to user interactions in real-time.

Why is DOM Manipulation Important?
It enables dynamic and interactive behavior in web pages, such as:
  > Showing/hiding elements.
  > Updating content without reloading the page.
  > Handling user input or events.
It plays a crucial role in frameworks/libraries like React, Angular, and Vue, which manage the DOM efficiently.

Real-Life Example:-
Imagine a button that shows or hides a message when clicked:
HTML:-
  <button id="toggleBtn">Toggle Message</button>
  <div id="message" style="display: none;">Hello, World!</div>

JS:-
  let button = document.getElementById("toggleBtn");
  let message = document.getElementById("message");
  
  button.addEventListener("click", () => {
      if (message.style.display === "none") {
          message.style.display = "block"; // Show the message
      } else {
          message.style.display = "none"; // Hide the message
      }
  });
